  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0ddd \u0dc3\u0da7\u0db1 \u0d85\u0dad\u0dca \u0db1\u0ddc\u0dc4\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The fighters do not give up the fight",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Galle Mouth activists say that the appointment of Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe to the office of President is against the public opinion and they will continue the struggle to remove him from office.",
        "Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe, who was defeated by the people of the country and came to parliament from the national list, cannot be accepted as the president, said Mr. Wasantha Mudalige, convener of the inter-university student body, representing the Galle Mudoora strugglers.",
        "He said this while attending a press conference held today at Gota Go Village, Aragal Bhoomi.",
        "Mr. Mudalige stated that it was the people who made Mr. Gotabhaya Rajapaksa, who got 69 lakh votes, flee to the Maldives by jet, and that the struggle cannot be ended by being beaten and chased away or arrested.",
        "Mr. Gotabhaya Rajapaksa appointed Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe as the Prime Minister to protect his family and fraud, Mr. Mudalige said that he is a person who did nothing for the people after being the Prime Minister for 6 times, looted the central bank, and was unable to enter the Parliament through a vote, and said that Mr. Mudalige will continue the struggle to oust him. . He said that the people's opinion is not represented in the parliament, and if they go outside the action plan given by the activists, the government can see what happens in the next two or three weeks.",
        "Sugathananda Thero of Tampitiya, Father Jeevantha Peiris, lawyer Nuwan Bopage, Lahiru Weerasekera, actor Jagath Manuvarna, Dumindu Hettiarachchi and others participated in this press conference representing the strugglers."
      ],
